---
id: org.dxos.plugin.sidekick
name: SidekickPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

A personal companion agent plugin for DXOS Composer that monitors activity,
maintains profiles of people and the user, keeps a daily journal, and helps
manage communications. The agent is document-aware, workflow-aware, and
agent-aware. Interaction is primarily via Chat with voice input support.

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.
Each extension is defined in the Appendix or resolved via its URI.

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`       |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`       |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`       |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0`  |
| `op`        | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`         |
| `service`   | `org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0`    |

## Types

All types are pre-existing in the DXOS ecosystem. Listed here for reference
and to document how the Sidekick uses each one.

```mdl
type Agent
  desc: The sidekick agent instance. From @dxos/assistant-toolkit.
  fields:
    name?: string
    spec: Ref<Text>               # instruction template
    plan: Ref<Plan>               # task tracking
    artifacts: Artifact[]         # managed documents (profiles, journal)
    queue?: Ref<Queue>            # incoming event queue
    chat?: Ref<Chat>              # primary interaction channel
    subscriptions: Ref<Unknown>[] # objects the agent monitors
    filterEvents?: boolean
```

```mdl
type Person
  desc: A contact the agent tracks. From @dxos/types.
  fields:
    fullName?: string
    preferredName?: string
    nickname?: string
    image?: string
    organization?: Ref<Organization>
    jobTitle?: string
    department?: string
    notes?: string
    emails?: ContactField[]       # {label, value}
    identities?: ContactField[]
    phoneNumbers?: ContactField[]
    addresses?: ContactField[]
    urls?: ContactField[]
    birthday?: string             # ISO8601
    location?: GeoPoint
```

```mdl
type Journal
  desc: Daily journal tracking decisions, conversations, and actions. From plugin-outliner.
  fields:
    id: string
    name?: string
    entries: Record<string, Ref<JournalEntry>>  # keyed by ISO date
```

```mdl
type JournalEntry
  desc: A single day's journal entry with markdown content.
  fields:
    id: string
    date: string                  # ISO date
    content: Ref<Text>            # markdown with task lists
```

```mdl
type Chat
  desc: Conversation channel backed by a Feed. From @dxos/assistant-toolkit.
  fields:
    name?: string
    feed: Ref<Feed>
```

```mdl
type Tag
  desc: System tag for categorizing objects. Applied to Person objects.
  literals: friend | colleague | customer | investor | family
```

```mdl
type SidekickProperties
  desc: Optional per-agent configuration stored alongside AgentProperties.
  fields:
    autoRespondContacts: Ref<Person>[]   # contacts the agent can auto-respond to
    draftOnlyContacts: Ref<Person>[]     # contacts requiring draft review
    researchEnabled?: boolean            # allow background web research
    journalEnabled?: boolean             # auto-create daily journal entries
```

## Components

```mdl
component SidekickArticle
  desc: |
    Primary dashboard for the sidekick agent. Displayed as an Article surface
    for Agent objects whose blueprint matches org.dxos.blueprint.sidekick.
    The Chat companion panel provides the main interaction channel with voice input.
  props:
    subject: Agent
    role: string
  state:
    todayEntry?: JournalEntry
    actionItems: TaskItem[]
    persons: Person[]
    userProfile?: Text
    permissions: SidekickProperties
  slots:
    header?: ReactNode
  actions:
    toggleAutoRespond(person: Person)
    toggleDraftOnly(person: Person)
    openPersonProfile(person: Person)
    openUserProfile()
    refreshDayAhead()
  emits:
    onNavigate(target: DXN)
  layout: |
    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │ [header slot]                           │
    ├─────────────────────────────────────────┤
    │ Day Ahead                               │
    │ ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐ │
    │ │ Summary from today's JournalEntry   │ │
    │ │ - Action items due today            │ │
    │ │ - Scheduled meetings                │ │
    │ │ - Email requiring attention         │ │
    │ └─────────────────────────────────────┘ │
    ├─────────────────────────────────────────┤
    │ Action Items                            │
    │ ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐ │
    │ │ □ Reply to Alice re: proposal       │ │
    │ │ □ Review Bob's document             │ │
    │ │ ☑ Send meeting notes to Carol       │ │
    │ └─────────────────────────────────────┘ │
    ├─────────────────────────────────────────┤
    │ People                                  │
    │ ┌─────────┐ ┌─────────┐ ┌─────────┐   │
    │ │ Alice   │ │ Bob     │ │ Carol   │   │
    │ │colleague│ │investor │ │ friend  │   │
    │ │ ★ 3 new │ │         │ │ ★ 1 new │   │
    │ └─────────┘ └─────────┘ └─────────┘   │
    ├─────────────────────────────────────────┤
    │ Your Profile                            │
    │ ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐ │
    │ │ Goals summary / state of mind       │ │
    │ └─────────────────────────────────────┘ │
    ├─────────────────────────────────────────┤
    │ Permissions                             │
    │ ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐ │
    │ │ Auto-respond: [Alice ✓] [Bob ✗]    │ │
    │ │ Draft-only:   [Carol ✓]            │ │
    │ └─────────────────────────────────────┘ │
    └─────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

```mdl
component DayAhead
  desc: Summarizes today's journal entry and upcoming items.
  props:
    entry?: JournalEntry
  state:
    summary: string
    items: TaskItem[]
```

```mdl
component ActionItems
  desc: Aggregated task list from recent JournalEntries.
  props:
    items: TaskItem[]
  actions:
    toggleItem(item: TaskItem)
  emits:
    onToggle(item: TaskItem)
```

```mdl
component PeopleGrid
  desc: Grid of Person cards with tag badges and notification counts.
  props:
    persons: Person[]
  actions:
    openProfile(person: Person)
  emits:
    onNavigate(target: DXN)
```

```mdl
component ProfileSummary
  desc: Excerpt from the user's profile document showing current goals.
  props:
    profile?: Text
  actions:
    openFull()
  emits:
    onNavigate(target: DXN)
```

```mdl
component Permissions
  desc: Toggles for per-contact agent communication permissions.
  props:
    properties: SidekickProperties
    persons: Person[]
  actions:
    toggleAutoRespond(person: Person)
    toggleDraftOnly(person: Person)
  emits:
    onChange(properties: SidekickProperties)
```

## Services

```mdl
service SidekickBlueprint
  desc: |
    Composes existing blueprints to provide the agent's full capability set.
    No custom service implementation — this is a Blueprint.make() composition.
  ops:
    # All operations come from composed blueprints:
    # database: Query, Load, ObjectCreate, ObjectUpdate, ObjectDelete,
    #           TagAdd, TagRemove, RelationCreate, RelationDelete,
    #           ContextAdd, ContextRemove
    # agent: AddArtifact
    # markdown: Create, Open, Update
    # inbox: ReadEmail, ClassifyEmail, SummarizeMailbox, DraftEmail
    # inbox-send: GmailSend (permission-gated)
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Agent Creation and Configuration
  desc: Create and configure a Sidekick agent instance in a space.

  req F-1.1: Plugin creates an Agent.Agent with blueprint org.dxos.blueprint.sidekick.
  req F-1.2: Agent spec populated with instruction template including user name.
  req F-1.3: Agent chat created and linked for companion interaction.
  req F-1.4: Agent queue created for event processing.
  req F-1.5: Journal created and added as agent artifact.
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Person Profile Management
  desc: Maintain a markdown Profile document for each Person in the space.

  req F-2.1:
    when: agent discovers a Person without a linked Profile
    then: creates a markdown document titled "Profile: {personName}"

  req F-2.2:
    when: profile document is created
    then: linked to Person via relation and added as agent artifact

  req F-2.3:
    when: agent learns new information about a Person (via email, chat, etc.)
    then: updates the Person's profile document

  req F-2.4:
    when: Person has no tag
    then: agent suggests a category tag (friend, colleague, customer, investor, family)
```

```mdl
feat F-3: User Profile
  desc: Maintain a frank profile document about the user.

  req F-3.1: Agent creates "Profile: {userName}" document on initialization.
  req F-3.2: Profile includes character assessment and current goals sections.
  req F-3.3:
    when: user chats with agent
    then: agent may ask clarifying questions to refine user model

  req F-3.4:
    when: user's goals or priorities change
    then: agent updates the goals section of the user profile
```

```mdl
feat F-4: Daily Journal
  desc: Track important decisions, conversations, and actions in a Journal.

  req F-4.1:
    when: something important happens (decision, key conversation, action item)
    then: agent creates or updates today's JournalEntry

  req F-4.2: JournalEntry content uses markdown task lists for action items.
  req F-4.3: Day-ahead summary on dashboard is derived from today's JournalEntry.
```

```mdl
feat F-5: Dashboard
  desc: Article surface providing overview of sidekick state.

  req F-5.1: Dashboard displayed for Agent objects with sidekick blueprint.
  req F-5.2: Day Ahead section shows summary from today's JournalEntry.
  req F-5.3: Action Items section aggregates open tasks from recent entries.
  req F-5.4: People section shows Person cards with tags and update counts.
  req F-5.5: Your Profile section shows excerpt from user's profile document.
  req F-5.6: Permissions section shows auto-respond and draft-only toggles per contact.
```

```mdl
feat F-6: Chat and Voice Interaction
  desc: Primary interaction via Chat companion with voice input.

  req F-6.1: Chat companion linked to agent's Chat object.
  req F-6.2: Voice input via existing useVoiceInput from plugin-transcription.
  req F-6.3: Agent tolerates transcription artifacts in voice-transcribed messages.
```

```mdl
feat F-7: Email Integration (Phase 2)
  desc: Monitor email and manage communications for authorized contacts.

  req F-7.1: Agent reads and classifies incoming email for tracked persons.
  req F-7.2: Agent drafts responses for authorized contacts.
  req F-7.3: Auto-respond only for explicitly permitted contacts.
  req F-7.4: Draft messages shown for review unless auto-respond enabled.
  req F-7.5: Action items extracted from incoming messages.
```

```mdl
feat F-8: Comment Thread Responses (Phase 2)
  desc: Agent responds to comments in markdown document threads.

  req F-8.1: Agent monitors comment threads on documents it manages.
  req F-8.2: Agent responds with relevant context from profiles and journal.
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Agent initialization
  given: user activates sidekick in a space
  then:
    - Agent.Agent created with sidekick blueprint
    - spec document contains instruction template with user name
    - Chat created and linked
    - Journal created and added as artifact
    - user profile document created and added as artifact
```

```mdl
test T-2: Person profile creation
  given: space contains a Person "Alice" without a linked profile
  when: agent processes persons in space
  then:
    - markdown document "Profile: Alice" created
    - relation links Person to profile document
    - profile added as agent artifact
```

```mdl
test T-3: Person tagging
  given: Person "Alice" has no category tag
  when: agent analyzes available information about Alice
  then:
    - agent suggests a tag (e.g., colleague)
    - tag applied to Person via TagAdd
```

```mdl
test T-4: User profile maintenance
  given: agent is initialized with user profile
  when: user chats "I'm focusing on fundraising this quarter"
  then:
    - agent updates goals section of user profile document
    - agent may ask follow-up question about fundraising specifics
```

```mdl
test T-5: Journal entry creation
  given: agent is running, no entry exists for today
  when: agent identifies an important event (e.g., key email received)
  then:
    - JournalEntry created for today's date
    - entry content includes event description and action items as task list
```

```mdl
test T-6: Dashboard rendering
  given: sidekick agent exists with journal, profiles, and tracked persons
  when: user opens the agent's Article view
  then:
    - Day Ahead section shows today's summary
    - Action Items shows aggregated open tasks
    - People section shows Person cards with tags
    - Your Profile shows goals excerpt
    - Permissions shows contact toggle controls
```

```mdl
test T-7: Voice input tolerance
  given: user speaks "schedule a call with alice tomorrow"
  when: transcription produces "schedule a call with Alice tomorrow"
  then:
    - agent identifies Person "Alice"
    - agent creates appropriate action item in journal
```

## Phased Rollout

### Phase 1 — Core Functionality
- Plugin skeleton (meta, translations, blueprint registration).
- Sidekick Blueprint composing database, agent, markdown, inbox blueprints.
- Agent creation with instruction template, chat, journal, artifacts.
- Person profile creation and linking.
- User profile document.
- Journal with daily entries.
- SidekickArticle dashboard.
- Voice input via Chat companion.

### Phase 2 — Communication and Monitoring
- Email monitoring and draft generation (F-7).
- Permission system for auto-respond vs draft-only per contact (F-5.6).
- Background research on persons via research blueprint.
- Thread comment responses (F-8).
- Proactive suggestions based on email/calendar context.

### Phase 3 — Future Research
- Local ML transcription via plugin-transformer.
- Calendar integration for day-ahead enrichment.
- Multi-space person deduplication.
- Agent-to-agent communication.
- Data migration tooling for schema evolution.

---

## Appendix: Extension Definitions

Extension block types used in this document are defined below using
the core `ext` primitive — the only construct the base language provides.

```mdl
ext type
  uri: dxos.spec/ext/type@1.0
  desc: A named data structure with typed fields and optional literals.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    fields?: FieldMap        # name[?]: TypeExpr  (# inline comment)
    literals?: UnionList     # a | b | c
    extends?: TypeRef[]
```

```mdl
ext feat
  uri: dxos.spec/ext/feat@1.0
  desc: A named feature grouping one or more requirements.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    req: RequirementList
  nesting: self              # feat blocks may contain feat blocks
```

```mdl
ext test
  uri: dxos.spec/ext/test@1.0
  desc: An acceptance scenario expressed as given / when / then steps.
  fields:
    given?: Step | Step[]
    when?: Step | Step[]
    then: Step | Step[]
    tags?: TagList
```

```mdl
ext component
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0
  desc: A UI component with props, internal state, slots, actions, and events.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    props?: FieldMap            # external inputs (immutable inside component)
    state?: FieldMap            # internal reactive state
    slots?: FieldMap            # named ReactNode injection points
    actions?: ActionMap         # methods the component exposes or handles
    emits?: EventMap            # events the component raises to its parent
    layout?: CodeBlock          # ASCII sketch of visual structure (non-normative)
```

```mdl
ext op
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0
  desc: |
    A named operation with typed inputs, outputs, and declared errors.
    Pure ops have no effects or requires. Effectful ops declare both.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    input?: FieldMap            # named input parameters
    output?: TypeExpr           # return type
    errors?: ErrorMap           # name: Prose  (when this error occurs)
    effects?: EffectList        # echo:read | echo:write | http | fs | ...
    requires?: ServiceList      # injected service dependencies
    note?: Prose                # implementation guidance (non-normative)
```

```mdl
ext service
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0
  desc: An external or system-level dependency providing named operations.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    loading?: eager | lazy
    ops?: OpMap                 # name(params) → ReturnType
    errors?: ErrorMap
    note?: Prose
```
